## 3. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

The following KPIs were developed to measure and track Egypt's energy performance:

|
 KPI                                     
|
 Description                                                                                             
|
|
---------------------------------------
|
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|
|
**
Import Dependency Ratio
**
|
 The proportion of energy consumed that is imported, as a percentage of total energy consumption.        
|
|
**
Energy Mix Diversity Index
**
|
 Measures the variety of energy sources in the energy mix (typically using the HHI index).               
|
|
**
Electricity Generation Diversity
**
|
 Measures the variety of sources in the electricity generation mix.                                        
|
|
**
Energy Intensity
**
|
 Measures the energy efficiency of the economy by calculating the ratio of TPES to GDP.                  
|
|
**
RE Share in FEC
**
|
 The share of Renewable Energy in the Total Final Consumption.                                           
|
|
**
RE Share in Electricity Generation
**
|
 The percentage of renewable energy in total electricity generation.                                     
|
|
**
Transmission & Distribution Losses
**
|
 Energy losses occurring during electricity transmission from power plants to end-users.                 
|
|
**
Electrification Rate
**
|
 The share of electricity in total final energy consumption.                                             
|

